# Validation Types

**CRITICAL**: Never use `module.exports` in validation type files. Just define variables.

## Available Validation Types

### Basic Data Types

- `string()` / `string(max)` / `string(min, max)` / `string(/regExp/)` - plain text
- `integer()` / `integer(max)` / `integer(min, max)` - whole numbers
- `float()` / `float(decimalPlaces)` / `float(max, decimalPlaces)` / `float(min, max, decimalPlaces)` - decimal numbers
- `number()` / `number(max)` / `number(min, max)` - any number
- `boolean()` - true/false
- `date()` / `date(format)` - date string (default `"%Y-%m-%d"`)
- `time()` / `time(format)` - time string (default `"%H:%M"`)
- `datetime()` / `datetime(format)` - datetime string (default `"%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%S.%L%Z"`)
- `shape({key: type, ...})` - key-value structure
- `array()` / `array(type)` / `array(type, min, max)` - array of items
- `map(keyType, valueType)` / `map(keyType, valueType, min, max)` - key-value map

### uuApp Data Types

- `id()` - uuApp object identifier (24 or 32 hex chars)
- `code()` - uuApp code (`/^[0-9a-zA-Z_]{3,64}$/`)
- `uri()` / `uri(absolute)` - URI string (max 1000 chars)
- `uuIdentity()` - uuIdentity identifier
- `uu5String()` / `uu5String(max)` / `uu5String(min, max)` - UU5 rich-text content (use only when needed)
- `uu5Json()` / `uu5Json(max)` - UU5 JSON string
- `binary()` - binary value (base64 or raw stream)
- `pageInfo()` - standard listing pagination shape
- `email()` - email address
- `objectCode()` - object code (`/^[a-zA-Z0-9_/\~&-.]{3,128}$/`)
- `base64()` - base64 encoded string
- `gps()` - GPS coordinates
- `constant(value)` - exact value match

### Functions

- `any()` - any type (always passes)
- `oneOf(["val0", "val1"])` - one of possible values or types
- `stringSetOf(["val0", "val1"])` - space-separated list of unique values from given set

Type naming convention: `{entityCamelCase}{UseCase}DtoInType` (e.g., `jokeCreateDtoInType`).

Modifier reference:

- `.isRequired()` - field is always required
- `.isRequired("otherField")` - required if `otherField` is not provided (conditional)
- `.isNotNull()` - if provided, cannot be null
